import java.nio.charset.Charset;
import java.util.zip.ZipEntry;

@RefinementAlias("ValidLevel(int level) { level >= 0 && level <= 9 }")
@ExternalRefinementsFor("java.util.zip.ZipOutputStream")
@StateSet({"closed", "entryopen", "finished", "open"})
public interface ZipOutputStreamRefinements {

    @StateRefinement(to = "open(this)")
    public void ZipOutputStream(OutputStream out);

    @StateRefinement(to = "open(this)")
    public void ZipOutputStream(OutputStream out, Charset charset);

    @StateRefinement(to = "closed(this)")
    public void close();

    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)", to = "open(this)")
    public void closeEntry();

    @StateRefinement(from = "open(this)", to = "finished(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)", to = "finished(this)")
    public void finish();

    @StateRefinement(from = "open(this)", to = "entryopen(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)")
    public void putNextEntry(ZipEntry e);

    @StateRefinement(from = "open(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)")
    public void setComment(String comment);

    @StateRefinement(from = "open(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)")
    public void setLevel(@Refinement("ValidLevel(level)") int level);

    @StateRefinement(from = "open(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)")
    public void setMethod(int method);

    @StateRefinement(from = "entryopen(this)")
    public void write(byte[] b, @Refinement("off >= 0") int off, @Refinement("len >= 0 && off + len <= b.length") int len);

}
```

Key design decisions made:

1. **`@RefinementAlias("ValidLevel")`**: The compression level is documented as 0-9 in the JSON, so a named alias `ValidLevel(int level) { level >= 0 && level <= 9 }` was created and applied to `setLevel`.

2. **`write` method refinements**: `off >= 0` ensures a valid non-negative start offset; `len >= 0 && off + len <= b.length` ensures the write region stays within array bounds, preventing `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException`.

3. **`setMethod`**: No refinement was added since the valid method constants (DEFLATED=8, STORED=0) are public but not linearly ordered in a way that can be expressed as a simple linear arithmetic predicate without knowledge of the exact constant values.

4. **`close()` without `from`**: The Mermaid diagram shows `close()` is reachable from all four states (Open, EntryOpen, Finished, and Closed), and the notes confirm it is idempotent, so no `from` constraint is applied.

